<hr />

<ul>
    <li>When sending family to the board or the black bag, they must come directly from the farmyard</li>
    <li>Coins can substitute for any influence cube</li>
    <li>Leftover coins are worth 1 point each</li>
    <li>Only family on the farmyard or visible on the board can die - not from church bag or yet to enter play</li>
    <li>Family memers die at <i>end</i> of turn - may even choose family who just performed the action</li>
    <li>Round end: last cube is taken from board</li>
    <li>If there are not enough cubes of a color to go into the bag, substitute cubes are <i>not</i> used</li>
    <li>May decline the chosen action (exception: Market)</li>
    <li><img src="~/lib/Images/Village/inn.png" class="icon" /> May play any number of Villager cards at any time during your turn</li>
    <li><img src="~/lib/Images/Village/port.png" class="icon" /> travel section of chronicle full <span class="arrow"></span> family that die in missionary church or ship are buried at sea, award points immediately</li>
    <li><img src="~/lib/Images/Village/port.png" class="icon" /> missionary church only becomes empty if the family member dies</li>
</ul>

<hr />

<h3>Mass</h3>
<ol>
    <li>Draw 4 figures from black bag
        <ul>
            <li>in clockwise order, each player may pay $1 per family to pick them from the bag (without randomly drawing)</li>
            <li>a total, and maximum, of 4 figures must be drawn</li>
            <li>undrawn family stay in bag for next round</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Move family up in church hierarchy
        <ul>
            <li>in clockwise order, pay grain to move as many family as you want & can afford up the church hierarchy</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Award 2 points to church majority
        <ul>
            <li>whoever has the most people at the church gets 2 points</li>
            <li>tie goes to the player who has the most advanced family</li>
            <li>further tie: all tied players get 2 points</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ol>

<hr />

